2. Legos are stacked in a pile with 24 Legos on the bottom row and 15 on the top row. There are 10 rows in all with each row having one more Lego than the one above it. How many Legos are in the stack?

- 24 on bottom
- 15 on top
- 10 rows total
- each row has one less lego than one below

$display(
f(0) = 24
)$

\
Explicit equation

$display(
f(r) = -1(r) + 24
)$

\
Recursive equation

$display(
f(r) = f(r-1) - 1
\
f(0)=24
)$

With $r$ representing row number starting count from 0

Total legos

$display(
sum _(r=0)^(9) f(r)
\
sum _(r=0)^(9) -r + 24 = 195
)$

